# Conventional Commit Message Template
# 
# Format: <type>[optional scope]: <description>
# 
# [optional body]
# 
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature (minor version bump)
#   fix:      A bug fix (patch version bump)
#   docs:     Documentation only changes (patch version bump)
#   style:    Changes that do not affect code meaning (patch version bump)
#   refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature (patch version bump)
#   perf:     A code change that improves performance (patch version bump)
#   test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests (patch version bump)
#   chore:    Changes to build process or auxiliary tools (patch version bump)
#   build:    Changes that affect the build system (patch version bump)
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts (patch version bump)
#   epoch:    Major architectural changes (epoch version bump)
#
# Breaking Changes:
#   - Add '!' after the type: feat!: breaking change
#   - Or include 'BREAKING CHANGE:' in the footer
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add new AI query endpoint
#   fix: resolve Canvas API timeout issue
#   feat!: change CLI interface completely
#   docs: update README with new setup instructions
#   chore: update dependencies to latest versions
#   perf(cli): optimize query response time
#   test: add unit tests for version management
#
# Current version info:
# Run: python3 version.py show
